# Word clouds for fake vs real news titles
def create_wordcloud(text_series, title, filename):
    text = " ".join(text_series.astype(str).tolist())
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', 
                          max_words=200, contour_width=3, contour_color='steelblue').generate(text)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title(title, fontsize=20)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(filename)
    plt.show()

# Create word clouds for fake and real news titles
create_wordcloud(df[df['label'] == 0]['title'], 'Word Cloud - Fake News Titles', 'wordcloud_fake.png')
create_wordcloud(df[df['label'] == 1]['title'], 'Word Cloud - Real News Titles', 'wordcloud_real.png')

# ----- TEXT PREPROCESSING ----- #
print("\n----- TEXT PREPROCESSING -----\n")

X = df.drop('label', axis=1)
y = df['label']

messages = X.copy()
messages.reset_index(inplace=True)

ps = PorterStemmer()
corpus = []

# Show a sample of preprocessing steps
sample_idx = 42
print(f"Original title (sample #{sample_idx}):")
print(messages['title'][sample_idx])

sample_review = re.sub('[^a-zA-Z]', ' ', messages['title'][sample_idx])
print("\nAfter removing non-alphabetic characters:")
print(sample_review)

sample_review = sample_review.lower()
print("\nAfter converting to lowercase:")
print(sample_review)

sample_review = sample_review.split()
print("\nAfter tokenization:")
print(sample_review)

sample_review = [ps.stem(word) for word in sample_review if not word in stopwords.words('english')]
print("\nAfter removing stopwords and stemming:")
print(sample_review)

sample_review = ' '.join(sample_review)
print("\nFinal processed text:")
print(sample_review)

----- TEXT PREPROCESSING -----

Original title (sample #42):
Trump says Brexit to be 'a great thing', wants quick trade deal with UK

After removing non-alphabetic characters:
Trump says Brexit to be  a great thing   wants quick trade deal with UK

After converting to lowercase:
trump says brexit to be  a great thing   wants quick trade deal with uk

After tokenization:
['trump', 'says', 'brexit', 'to', 'be', 'a', 'great', 'thing', 'wants', 'quick', 'trade', 'deal', 'with', 'uk']

After removing stopwords and stemming:
['trump', 'say', 'brexit', 'great', 'thing', 'want', 'quick', 'trade', 'deal', 'uk']

Final processed text:
trump say brexit great thing want quick trade deal uk

print("\nProcessing all titles...")
for i in range(len(messages)):
    if i % 5000 == 0:
        print(f"Processing title {i}/{len(messages)}")
    review = re.sub('[^a-zA-Z]', ' ', messages['title'][i])
    review = review.lower()
    review = review.split()
    review = [ps.stem(word) for word in review if not word in stopwords.words('english')]
    review = ' '.join(review)
    corpus.append(review)

print("Text preprocessing completed.")

# ----- MODEL PREPARATION ----- #
print("\n----- MODEL PREPARATION -----\n")

voc_size = 5000
print(f"Vocabulary size: {voc_size}")

# One-hot encoding
onehot_repr = [one_hot(words, voc_size) for words in corpus]

# Padding sequences
sent_length = 20
embedded_docs = pad_sequences(onehot_repr, padding='pre', maxlen=sent_length)
print(f"Shape of padded sequences: {embedded_docs.shape}")

# Prepare final data
X_final = np.array(embedded_docs)
y_final = np.array(y)

# Split data
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_final, y_final, test_size=0.33, random_state=42)
print(f"Training set shape: {X_train.shape}, {y_train.shape}")
print(f"Testing set shape: {X_test.shape}, {y_test.shape}")

# ----- MODEL BUILDING ----- #
print("\n----- MODEL BUILDING -----\n")

# Create callbacks for better training
early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=3, restore_best_weights=True)
model_checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint('best_model.keras', monitor='val_accuracy', save_best_only=True, mode='max')

# Build model
embedding_vector_features = 40
model = Sequential()
model.add(Embedding(voc_size, embedding_vector_features, input_length=sent_length))
model.add(Bidirectional(LSTM(100)))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])

print(model.summary())

# ----- MODEL TRAINING ----- #
print("\n----- MODEL TRAINING -----\n")

# Train model
history = model.fit(
    X_train, y_train,
    validation_data=(X_test, y_test),
    epochs=10,
    batch_size=64,
    callbacks=[early_stopping, model_checkpoint]
)

print("\n----- FEATURE IMPORTANCE ANALYSIS -----\n")

# Extract the embedding layer weights
embedding_weights = model.layers[0].get_weights()[0]

# Create a dictionary of words
vocab_dict = {}
for i, doc in enumerate(corpus):
    for word in doc.split():
        if word not in vocab_dict and len(vocab_dict) < voc_size:
            vocab_dict[word] = len(vocab_dict)

# Reverse the dictionary to map indices to words
index_to_word = {v: k for k, v in vocab_dict.items()}

# Get the words with the highest embedding values (rough estimate of importance)
embedding_sum = np.sum(np.abs(embedding_weights), axis=1)
top_indices = np.argsort(embedding_sum)[-20:]  # Get top 20 indices

print("Top words by embedding weight magnitude:")
for idx in reversed(top_indices):
    if idx in index_to_word:
        print(f"{index_to_word[idx]}: {embedding_sum[idx]:.4f}")

# ----- PREDICTION EXAMPLES ----- #
print("\n----- PREDICTION EXAMPLES -----\n")

# Function to preprocess a new title
def preprocess_title(title):
    review = re.sub('[^a-zA-Z]', ' ', title)
    review = review.lower()
    review = review.split()
    review = [ps.stem(word) for word in review if not word in stopwords.words('english')]
    review = ' '.join(review)
    return review

# Function to predict if a news title is fake or real
def predict_fake_news(title):
    processed_title = preprocess_title(title)
    onehot_title = one_hot(processed_title, voc_size)
    padded_title = pad_sequences([onehot_title], padding='pre', maxlen=sent_length)
    prediction = model.predict(padded_title)[0][0]
    return prediction

# Select a few examples from the test set
sample_indices = np.random.choice(range(len(X_test)), 5, replace=False)

print("Prediction Examples:")
for i, idx in enumerate(sample_indices):
    # Get the original title from the dataset
    sample_idx = np.where((X_final == X_test[idx]).all(axis=1))[0][0]
    original_title = messages['title'][sample_idx]
    
    # Make prediction
    prediction = model.predict(X_test[idx:idx+1])[0][0]
    actual_label = y_test[idx]
    
    print(f"\nExample {i+1}:")
    print(f"Title: {original_title}")
    print(f"Prediction: {prediction:.4f} ({'Real News' if prediction > 0.5 else 'Fake News'})")
    print(f"Actual: {'Real News' if actual_label == 1 else 'Fake News'}")
    print(f"{'✓ Correct' if (prediction > 0.5) == actual_label else '✗ Incorrect'}")

print("\nAnalysis complete!")
